728255f-a.title: Queens: Wyckoff Avenue - Putnam Avenue
728255f-a.text:
Wyckoff Ave., north side, west from Putnam Ave. (right foremround)
to Madison Street, showing the Antresch Bairy house and grounds of 1870
at the corner. Later it was Elein's Deutschland Park. Reimels, son-in-
law of Welr and brothsr-in-law of 2erwick, operated it at one time.
This house was demolished in October 1927. The only houses standing in
this view in 1929 are the two displaying awninas, and which are numbered
781-783 Wyckoff Ave. A 5-story brick building now occupies the corner
in the foreground.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
